President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Robert D. Hormats was nominated for Under Secretary of State for Economic, Energy, and Agricultural Affairs at the Department of State. Hormats has a long history in the government and finance sectors, including serving as Assistant Secretary of State for Economic and Business Affairs and Vice Chairman of Goldman Sachs (International). Gary S. Guzy was nominated for Deputy Director of the Office of Environmental Quality (Council on Environmental Quality). Guzy has 25 years of environmental leadership experience and currently serves as General Counsel of APX, Inc. Lee A. Feinstein was nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Poland at the Department of State. Feinstein has held various positions in government, academia, and think tanks, including serving as a Senior Advisor in the Office of the Secretary at the Department of State and Deputy Director of Studies at the Council on Foreign Relations.